node.text:
ROOM REVEAL…6 years in the making😅 (swipe for THAT before). But…the final decision I am torn: which rug? Help me!
Rug 1: spunky red
Rug 2: tranquil beauty 

On another note, I feel like I love every angle of this room now that the windows have been redone with spray paint and pvc trim. Total game changer right? 

Sharing all the details and sources in my stories tonight!

node.text:
I can FINALLY share what I was filming for!…my first ever commercial partnering with Omaze to announce your chance to win THIS gorgeous 2.6 million dollar dream home in Miami (or take the cash option of 1.8 million dollars). I know😳, I think it’s freaking cool too and I can’t believe I got to be a part of it (swipe for more photos and awkward poses😉).

And my favorite part, every donation supports Make A Wish @makeawishamerica , one of my favorite non profits that is near and dear to my heart. 

Filming all the content for this dream home was honestly, a dream come true…thanks for being excited with me!

And…
If you want to enter for your chance to win this Dream Home (and if you win, invite me over!), click the link in my bio or go to omaze.com/angelarose.
**use my code ANGELA300 when you enter for an extra 300 entries🙌🏻.
@omaze #ad

node.text:
BLACK WINDOW transformation DRAMA…but was it worth it??? (Swipe) The elements were against me today(see stories😳)⚡️💨💧, and you saw me TICKED…but I still don’t regret removing the shutters and changing the windows to black with this super cool pvc trim.

Sorry for those of you TEAM shutter friends that I upset by removing them, you forgive me? You at least feel bad for me after watching my stories…right?🤣🤣🤣

Now to redo the rest of the windows…only 7 more in this room😳.

Finically finished (swipe)!!! Only 2 years in the making😅, and the fluffy brick wall and painted black windows are the perfect final touch! 

Totally the right call to extend that brick wall alllllll the way from the kitchen to the fireplace right? Right. 😉

*and YES, my kids got tired of me taking photos and told me they were just gonna stay (for that last photo)🤣.

GIVING AWAY $2000 ($1000 to 2 of you) to close off kitchen reveal week!!! I wanted to do something just from me to you to say thank you for you excitement and support throughout this kitchen renovation❤️. And so to help you with YOUR projects, I am going to pick…

2 people 
$1000 each 

❤️To ENTER: 
1. Like and comment on this post 
***extra entries if you like my last 3 kitchen reveal posts.

(if you want, tell me what projects you’d love to work on next!)

THANK YOU! Thank you, with all my heart. Love you guys.🤍🤍🤍

node.text:
KITCHEN reveal part 3: the view that made me cry😭. Those shelves you guys!!! How was I on the fence about them??? They are the perfect finale to this kitchen. Standing from this view and seeing that stormy backsplash, the @smegusa range, the soft fluffy brick, the painted black windows, the custom island, the DIY hood, the shelves…I love it. Every detail. 

Deep breath. What’s your favorite feature? And can you spot the funny thing I added???

Speaking of details:

Appliances: 48” dual fuel @smegusa Portofino Range in stainless steel (5 gas burners). 24” Fully Integrated Panel Ready @smegusa Dishwasher (to keep dishwasher hidden with a panel) #MySMEGKitchen #SMEGpartner

Cabinets: I kept existing boxes and refaced with custom door fronts in Angela Rose Slim Shaker Dream Dusk from @nieucabinetdoors 

Countertops: Danby marble (sourced from Vermont)

I am so proud of this angle of the kitchen…and it’s DONE! Whew!

node.text:
KITCHEN reveal (part 1)!!! I’m not crying YOU’RE crying😭😭😭. (Swipe for before and then close up angles of this shot). Started this kitchen in January, and it’s been a long, fun, challenging, and emotional journey. But it’s DONE. And it’s beautiful. And I LOVE it. 

Thank you for being here and cheering me on through the process. With all my heart, thank you❤️. 

*stay tuned over the next couple days for the reveal of all the other angles!!! And see stories for details.

I. LOVE. THIS. So much. Thank you for allowing me to do this and cheering us on❤️❤️❤️. 

Do you love it?
